@startuml
title Use Case 4: Sending a Message

actor Sender as "User (Sender)"
boundary GUI as "Client GUI"
boundary cGUI as "Recipient GUI"
control Client as "Client App"
control Recipient as "Recipient Client"
control Server as "Server"
collections Cache as "Server Cache"

== Compose and send ==
Sender -> GUI: Type message\nClick "Send"
GUI -> Client: PassMessage(MessageObject)
Client -> Client: Update local conversation
Client --> GUI: Repaint conversation
Client -> Server: SendMessage(MessageObject)

== Server processing ==
ref over Sender, cGUI, Server, Cache, Recipient : Push New Message
@enduml
